race.comment: ELLIPSIS (5) recorded her sixth top three finish from seven starts when she held on well for third in a BM78 over this distance at Randwick Saturday week ago. Only goes up 2kgs in what looks a far easier assignment. Will race handy and prove very tough to overcome. IL PASSERO (8) has run a couple of similar races to launch this prep, coming from well off the speed on straightening then quickening nicely to fill a minor placing. Will enjoy sitting off an anticipated strong tempo here - watch for him late. BEREZKA (4) returns from a 20-week spell. Closed last prep with a couple of fine efforts in better races than this. Two recent trials should have her forward enough to run a big race. This is a touch short for SISTER DAAE (6) but while fresh she is capable of a bold showing. Market watch on KOMODO DRAGON (2) who is smart enough to mix it with these but does come off a 14-month lay-off.
